<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-06-24T23:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-06-24T23:00:00-05:00" n="653" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d653">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">693.003/566: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Reinsch</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-06-25T12:00:00+08:00"><hi rend="italic">June 25,
                                            1919, noon</hi>.</date><lb/>[<hi rend="italic">Received
                                        June 25, 9.23 a.m.</hi>]</dateline></opener>
                            <p>All other powers concerned having accepted the revised import tariff
                                the provisional acceptance authorized by your telegram of March
                                27th, 6 p.m.<note n="87" xml:id="d653fn87"><hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_657">p. 657</ref>.</note> was
                                communicated to the Foreign Office on June 9th. The Chinese Foreign
                                Office has now notified the several Legations that the revised
                                tariff will be published on July 1st and put into effect from August
                                1st.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Reinsch</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>